 NEW YORK South African comedian Trevor Noah has bought an apartment in Manhattan for $10-million (R130m), the Washington Post has reported.The three-bedroomed penthouse was reportedly found by his girlfriend Jordyn Taylor.The apartment apparently has an amazing view, a wrap-around terrace and lots of space to entertain guests. Sotheby's describes the penthouse at Stella Tower as "a gem atop a masterpiece""This magnificent 3 bedroom, 3 bath and 2 half bath residence has been thoughtfully laid out for the ultimate form of luxury living. This one-of-a-kind penthouse is the epitome of grandeur; boasting 14ft (4,26m) ceiling heights, approx 3,596 sq ft (334 square metre) interior and a 934 sq ft private terrace (86,7 square metre)." eNCA